Installation Instructions

To get started, you have to compile chatnut-server. For compiling, 
you need to have make and gcc with C++ support installed.

Run the command

make

in this directory to build chatnut-server. Next, run the command

make install

to install chatnut-server. This will copy the executable file to 
/usr/local/bin. Optionally, you can run the command

make clean

to remove all object files and the executable from the src folder.

Feel free to contact the developer with any questions concerning 
the compilation or installation of chatnut-server.
